Fluid Mechanics
---------------

*   **Experimental Fluid Dynamics (EFD)** wind tunnels, towing tank, flume, field experiments.
*   **Theoretical Fluid Dynamics**
*   **Computaional Fluid Dynamics (CFD)** numerical algorithms, computers, visualization, animations.

Classification of fluid flows
-----------------------------

Beofre start to write the code and run the simulation, we need to define our fluid flows in pratical engineering problems properly. Here gives a flow chart to choose the properties of fluid flows step by step:

\[latex\]\\eqalign{ \\begin{bmatrix}Newtonian \\\\non - Newtonian\\\\ rarefied \\quad gas\\end{bmatrix}\\cdot \\begin{bmatrix}single \\quad phase \\\\multi-phase\\\\ fluid/structure\\\\ particle-ladden\\end{bmatrix}\\cdot \\begin{bmatrix}steady \\\\transient\\\\ harmonic\\end{bmatrix}\\cdot \\begin{bmatrix}1D,2D,3D\\\\axisymmetric\\\\rotationally\\\\symmetric\\end{bmatrix} }\[/latex\]

\[latex\]\\eqalign{ \\begin{bmatrix}immersed\\\\surface-piercing\\\\submerged\\end{bmatrix}\\cdot \\begin{bmatrix}inviscid\\\\laminar\\\\turbulent\\\\transitional\\end{bmatrix}\\cdot \\begin{bmatrix}incompressible\\\\subsonic\\\\transonic\\\\supersonic\\\\htpersonic\\end{bmatrix}\\cdot \\begin{bmatrix}rotational\\\\irrotational\\end{bmatrix}\\cdot }\[/latex\]

\[latex\]\\eqalign{ \\begin{bmatrix}bounded/internal\\\\unbounded/external\\\\mixed\\end{bmatrix}\\cdot \\begin{bmatrix}conduction\\\\convection\\\\radiation\\end{bmatrix} }\[/latex\]

* * *

Discretization of fluid
-----------------------

\[latex\] \\begin{equation} \\stackrel{\\mbox{for each fluid particle }}{ \\begin{bmatrix} Conservation of Mass \\\\ Conservation of Momentum \\\\ Conservation of Energy \\\\ Equation of state\\\\ Fourier's law, \\quad etc. \\end{bmatrix} }\\Rightarrow \\stackrel{\\stackrel{\\mbox{for each}}{\\mbox{numerical element}}}{ \\begin{bmatrix} U,V,W \\\\ p \\\\ \\rho \\\\ T\\\\ \\overline{u\_iu\_j},\\overline{u\_ip'} \\end{bmatrix} }\\Rightarrow \\stackrel{\\stackrel{\\mbox{discrete}}{\\mbox{nodal value}}}{ \\begin{bmatrix} lift/drag \\ force \\\\ moments \\\\ flowrate \\\\ flow \\ separation\\\\ heat \\ transder\\\\ efficiency \\end{bmatrix}} \\end{equation} \[/latex\]

* * *

Procedure of CFD
----------------

The computational fluid dynamics start from listing all essential partial differential equations (PDE) for the problem. Then, discretizing the PDE into system of algebrabic equations depends on the schemes we implement, such as **finite difference**, **finite volume**, **finite element method**. By solving systems of linear equations in matrix form, we obtain the numerical solutions. ![](data:image/png;base64,)
